The '''Seiddab Trilogy''' is a series of video games designed by [[Steve Turner (game programmer)|Steve Turner]] (as [[Graftgold]]) for the [[ZX Spectrum]] and published by [[Hewson Consultants]]. It consists of '''''[[3D Space-Wars]]''''' (1983),<ref>{{WoS game|name=3D Space-Wars|id=0004686}}</ref> '''''3D Seiddab Attack''''' (1984),<ref>{{WoS game|name=3D Seiddab Attack|id=0004393}}</ref> and '''''3D Lunattack'''''.<ref>{{WoS game|name=3D Lunattack|id=0002955}}</ref> All three games were later published together as '''''The Seiddab Trilogy''''' by Hewson for the [[Rotronics Wafadrive]].<ref>{{WoS game|id=0019031}}</ref> The series name is derived from the word "baddies" being spelt in reverse.

'''''Astroclone''''' (1985), also written by Turner is part of this series.<ref>{{WoS game|id=0000299}}</ref>

